cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for pixelwise classification on images, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes novel algorithms for efficient forward and backward propagation of CNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of GPUs for efficient computation, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
